# Server caching + Postgres pool (locked)

## Non-negotiables

- **`READ_THROUGH_CACHE_ENABLED` defaults to `true`.** Setting it to `false` in any environment other than a one-off benchmark silently disables every read-through cache wrapper in the codebase (`branches.list`, `roleTemplates.list`, `voip.isEnabled`, `permissions.listTemplateBaselines`, `settings.getSystemSettings`, `audit.actorFilterOptions`, `settings.getNotificationEmailConfig`, `users.getMyNotificationPreferences`, `/auth/me` user bundle, dashboard CEO overview, products, logistics, orders, messaging). When disabled: simple reads go from <50ms back to **1–9s** under burst load. **Do not commit `READ_THROUGH_CACHE_ENABLED=false` to any deployable env file.** The kill-switch is a perf-debug tool only.
- **Postgres pool config in `apps/api/src/database/database.module.ts` is tuned, not arbitrary.** Defaults: `max: 30`, `idle_timeout: 300`, `max_lifetime: 1800`, `connect_timeout: 30`, `application_name: 'yannis-api'`, plus an eager warmup that fires `max` parallel `SELECT 1`s at module init so every slot pays its TCP+TLS handshake before the first user request. **Do not lower `idle_timeout` back to 10s** (was killing connections between dashboard clicks → 200–500ms TLS re-handshake on every burst). **Do not remove the warmup** (cold-pool first-page-load tax was visible to users).
- **Every cached read MUST have an explicit invalidation hook** wired into every mutation that changes its underlying data. The pattern is `invalidateXxxCache()` helper functions defined alongside the cache wrapper, called from each mutation handler. Stale-data bugs caused by missing invalidation are the #1 risk this architecture trades safety for; the discipline is the price.
- **Page-loader fan-outs are bundled.** Twelve `*PageBundle` tRPC procedures (in `marketing.router.ts`, `orders.router.ts`, `inventory.router.ts`, `finance.router.ts`) replace what used to be 4–14 parallel HTTP round-trips per page load. **Do not revert a Remix loader to firing the constituent calls separately** — the bundle reduces network/middleware/auth overhead and is the canonical shape going forward.

