## TTLs (default; override in code only with reason)

| Endpoint | TTL | Invalidation trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `/auth/me` user bundle | 60s | every user / role / template / permissions write (see `user-bundle-cache.service.ts` invalidation list) |
| `branches.list` | 15 min | branch create/update/archive |
| `roleTemplates.list` | wrapped via Redis | role-template CRUD |
| `voip.isEnabled` | 60s | `voip.setEnabled` |
| `permissions.listCatalog` | 60s (in-memory, immune to env flag) | none — boot-time only writes |
| `permissions.listTemplateBaselines` | wrapped via Redis | role-template / catalog mutations |
| `settings.getSystemSettings` | 60s | every system settings mutation |
| `settings.getNotificationEmailConfig` | 5 min | `updateNotificationEmailConfig` |
| `audit.actorFilterOptions` | 5 min (scoped by org/branch) | none (5min staleness acceptable) |
| `users.getMyNotificationPreferences` | 5 min (per-user) | `updateMyNotificationPreferences` |
| `dashboard.ceoOverview` | 60s | none (60s freshness acceptable) |

## Operational rules

- **When wrapping a new cached endpoint:** add a `setXxxCacheService` setter, wire it in `trpc.module.ts::onModuleInit`, define an `invalidateXxxCache(...)` helper, and call it from every mutation that touches the cached data.
- **Pool sizing for multi-process deploys:** set `PG_MAX_CONNECTIONS=10` per process (4 procs × 10 = 40, well under Cloud SQL's 100-connection default ceiling). Default of 30 is sized for single-process dev / single-replica prod.
- **Reading the timing logs:** `db > total` on a bundle = parallel queries summing more than wall-clock = healthy. `db ≈ total` on a single endpoint = the query itself is slow (look for missing indexes). `db = 0ms` with sub-50ms `total` = Redis cache hit (the win).

## Do NOT

- Do **NOT** flip `READ_THROUGH_CACHE_ENABLED=false` in any deployable env. It is for one-off benchmarking only.
- Do **NOT** await N notification creates / external sends on a mutation hot path; use the existing `enqueueCreate*` / `void notifications.create(...).then(...)` pattern (see CLAUDE.md → Push Notification Center).
- Do **NOT** add a new `getOrSet` wrapper without also wiring the matching `invalidate` call in every mutation that changes the cached data — stale data caused by missing invalidation is the chief risk this architecture accepts.
- Do **NOT** revert the postgres-js pool config (`max: 30`, `idle_timeout: 300`, `max_lifetime: 1800`, eager warmup) without measuring impact. The defaults were chosen to remove specific observed pathologies (saturation → 6–9s queue waits, idle close → TLS re-handshake on burst).
- Do **NOT** un-bundle a Remix loader back into N parallel `apiRequest(...)` calls. The `*PageBundle` shape is the canonical pattern.
